9:
That's enough, Shota! We don't have
to fight!
15: Shut UP. You're so DAMN ANNOYING!
33:
Stay right where you are! Don't
move a muscle!
37:
Who the hell do you think you are,
huh?!
43:
If it's a fight you want, it's a fight
you'll get. But don't think I'll go easy
on you just because you're a stupid,
snot-nosed brat.
63:
I thought you two were friends, even
back then...
68: You always were blinder than a bat...
71:
Only seeing what you want to see...
Pretending like you don't know the
truth because it's more convenient
that way!
73:
All so you can keep up the
appearance of being a good
teacher!
82:
This is no time for banter! We need
to leave!
90:
Everything will be all right, Shota
Inori. We do not abandon our own.
93:
You have only just awakened your
powers.
95:
Have patience. We can share in our
dreams together.
112:
Now that we have a moment to
breathe, we should finish explaining
the plan.
116:
Seiji. Nao. We'll be taking you to our
home base.
125:
I can't come with. I have to find the
lance.
127:
To do that, I'll need to go knocking
on the Starsayers' door.
132:
You truly are remarkable... I'm
ashamed that I can't even match
half your courage.
135:
Despite being the adult here, all I've
done is cower in fear.
143:
I've made a huge mess of Ayumu
Nagihara's life...
147:
And I have no idea what to do about
it.
152:
I pretty much have a million
questions and no answers.
155:
Like... Who were Shota and Yuki to
Ayumu?
159:
When I was your teacher in middle
school...
161:
You were a loner, never making the
effort to socialize with others.
166: This guy, a loner? I don't believe it.
169:
It's not as strange as you might
think. Children will often pick
someone to ostracize, sometimes
for no reason in particular...
176:
The first to be targeted was Yuki
Mishima.
179: Before I could figure out what to do...
181: You think so too, right, Ayumu?
186:
If you want to gossip, find someone
who cares.
188:
...Wow. Fine, be that way. See if we
care.
191:
Your classmates started ignoring
you after that, but you almost
seemed to prefer that treatment.
194:
It was only after summer vacation
that things changed. That was when
Shota joined our school.
197:
He paid no attention to the rest of
the class and did what he liked,
which included talking to you.
200:
He'd bug you about the week's
newest manga chapters and stuff
like that.
203:
You called him a weirdo who didn't
know how to read the mood and
complained about him every day.
210:
You started smiling more after
meeting Shota. I sincerely believed
you two had a good relationship...
214:
As for Yuki, you guys became friends
after getting into high school.
216:
You didn't really get along with girls,
but Yuki was an exception.
219:
That really bothered Sho, but... Don't
tell him I told you that.
223:
So let me get this straight—while all
that crap was going down with the
kids, you just stood there and
watched?
226: And you call yourself a teacher.
231:
...Like I said, I'm ashamed that I can't
even match half Ayumu's courage...
then and now.
236:
Somehow I'm not surprised to hear
you say that...
242:
Antibodies! Get ready to fight, Alk!
Nimbus!
